ABOUT:
Leaf Blast is an early-stage infection of rice blast fungi. It primarily damages young leaf tissue leading to characteristic lesions.

SYMPTOMS:
Diamond-shaped spots on leaves
Grayish centers with dark borders
Wilting of young leaves
Irregular dead patches on fields

PREVENTION:
Improve field aeration by proper spacing
Avoid heavy nitrogen application
Use resistant varieties
Apply Tricyclazole during early infection
